						<div class="postbody">Hello <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> <br /><br />I have now a question about background rendering<br /><br />I know that the background rendering starts 2 tiles ahead before the real output of the tile<br /><br />according to the this <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/images/d/d1/Ntsc_timing.png">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/images/d/d1/Ntsc_timing.png</a><!-- m --> <br /><br />we fetch the first two tiles of scanline (S) in clks from 321 -&gt; 336 of scanline (S-1)<br /><br />according to this project , the address of the name table byte is as follows ( assuming we are dealing with name table at 0x2C00 )<br /><br />&amp; = concatenation <br />&quot;1011&quot; &amp;  y_scroll[7:3] &amp;  x_scroll[7:3] <br /><br />where x_scroll and y_scroll are counters for horizontal and vertical pixels<br /><br />the problem I see with this is that the first 2 tiles are not fetched right <br /><br />as example , if we are on scanline y=0x02 thefore the address if name table byte( at clk = 321) will be equal <br />0x2C08(the ninth tile) not 0x2C00( the first tile )</div>

